{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e5be25b5-0454-4891-9d9a-0093bb67c2f2","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading files via property functions runs during **every evaluation** (IDE refreshes, restore, build). This blocks the evaluation thread with synchronous I/O. **Fix:** Move content reading to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs at build time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Overly Broad Glob Pattern (Medium Impact)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThis walks the **entire directory tree** on every evaluation. If the project directory grows (e.g., `node_modules`, large asset folders), evaluation time will spike. **Fix:** Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to prune known-large directories, or narrow the glob to specific extensions.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Chained Import Depth (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels of nested imports add evaluation overhead. While manageable at 3 levels, this pattern can compound quickly in larger repos. Each import is a separate file open + parse + evaluation pass.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Recommendation |\n|-------|----------|----------------|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | High | Move to a build-time target |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Medium | Narrow scope or add exclusions |\n| Nested import chain | Low | Flatten if it grows further |\n\nThe file I/O property function is the biggest offender — it introduces disk latency into every single evaluation cycle.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"94b727ee-1fc5-4b4f-a266-833aec72ec79","outputTokens":434,"requestId":"1C49:2CF140:C097A0:E168B5:69F40141"},"id":"7590be90-e816-4a63-879f-e7f4771718b1","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:26:40.133Z","parentId":"8a8b52eb-2224-4ef5-b045-c36b32c28328"}
